<title>Supply Curve for Jackets for Snowboarders</title>
<media id="bmedia-011" alt="The horizontal x axis is labeled quantity, and is labeled from left to right, 0 to 1,400 in increments of 200. The vertical y axis is labeled price, and is labeled, from bottom to top, 0 dollars to 200 dollars in increments of $25. Points are plotted on the graph, and connected with a solid line. The points are plotted at approximately 275, $40, and 450, $60, and 700, $80, and 800, $100, and 975, $120, and 1100, $135, and 1325, $155. A dashed horizontal line extends from 100 dollars on the y axis, and a vertical dashed line extends from 800 on the x axis and meet at the plotted point 800, $100.">
